President Muhammadu Buhari met with Godwin Emefiele, governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), on Sunday, to discuss the deadline for the swap of old naira notes. Emefiele visited Buhari in his hometown, Daura, Katsina state. After the meeting, the CBN governor announced the extension of the deadline from January 31, 2023 to February 10. Here are photos from the meeting. President Muhammadu Buhari receives Godwin Emefiele, CBN governor as president approves 10 days to exchange old naira notes for new one in Daura, Katsina State. Photo: Sunday Aghaeze      